🔹 Configure Form

Configure Form allows administrators or users with permissions to modify the structure and layout of a form.

Features
Add or remove fields
Rearrange field positions
Create sections
Modify form layout
Control field visibility
Benefits
Improves form organization
Displays only relevant information
Enhances user efficiency
Supports customization
Example

Right-click form header → Configure → Form Layout

🔹 Personalize Form

Personalize Form allows individual users to customize how a form appears only for themselves without affecting others.

Features
Show or hide fields
Rearrange visible fields
User-specific customization
Changes apply only to personal view
Benefits
Cleaner interface
Faster access to important fields
Better user experience
No impact on global configuration
Example

Open a form → Click Settings (Gear Icon) → Personalize → Form

🔹 Difference Between Configure Form & Personalize Form
Configure Form	Personalize Form
Changes form layout	Changes personal view
Can affect all users	Affects only current user
Requires configuration permissions	User-level customization
Add/remove form fields	Show/hide fields
